content.description:
Might as well give it a shot since you are in the area.

Somewhat powerful and awkward.
content.protection: just a pad or two is fine
content.location: On the South facing corner of the boulder behind the Contact problem. Start sitting on a left facing flake and climb out of the bulge

content.description:
start matched on crescent gaston/sidepull in steep cave slap out to arete.

this I believe is the original stinkeye start and original grade, rock quality and grade are equally soft

Start standing with your left hand on a sidepull at 5 feet and your right hand on the lip of the boulder. Make a couple moves up and left and then rock over to establish yourself on the slab. Finish up the easy slab on somewhat questionable rock (especially near the top).

Not a lot of moves, but the movement and the holds are quite enjoyable.

Given v7 in the book. Feels a lot easier.
content.location: Located on the boulder directly across from 'Contact'. This problem faces 'Contact'.

content.description: Stand start.  Climb the arete using sidepulls and horizontal seams to an easy top out.
content.location: The arete/face just to the left of Contact

content.description: Start on a sidepull in a crack and head left to an undercling jug.  Use slopers to work your way to a high pinch then keep moving left until it's obviously time to climb up.  After you hit the rail at the top of the boulder, move back right and top it out.
content.location: Contact faces East and is located on the boulder closest to the main approach trail.

content.description: Start on crimps, slap to jug around arete follow jugs up. Felt pretty soft for the grade, first move takes a little juice. Could probably be climbed straight up for bonus points
content.location: directly behind contact you can see the starting crimps on the left side of an arete

content.description: Grab left facing flake and throw (DIRECTLY) for the point/corner - Original beta form the Black Bible for the v6
